多国出现医院聚集性感染事件。
Aggregate hospital infections occur in many countries.
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
澎湃新闻记者 胡甄卿 闫颂阳新冠肺炎疫情逐渐在多国扩散。
The epidemic of Yan Yan-song Yangxincang pneumonia is spreading in many countries.
由于易感人群密集，韩国、美国等国的护理机构和医院出现了新冠肺炎聚集性感染，美国一家护理中心多名老人因感染新冠肺炎死亡，联邦机构已经介入调查。
As a result of high population density, care institutions and hospitals in South Korea and the United States, among others, have developed pneumonic crowns, and federal agencies have stepped in to investigate the deaths of several elderly people from a care center in the United States as a result of pneumonia.
在护理机构和医院长期住宿的病人或老年人由于免疫力低下、有基础疾病，因新冠肺炎死亡的风险更高。
Patients or elderly people living in long-term care institutions and hospitals are at higher risk of death from coronary pneumonia due to low immunity and underlying diseases.
同时，医护人员被感染或隔离则可能造成人手短缺，对医疗系统产生不利影响。
At the same time, the infection or isolation of health-care workers may result in a shortage of staff, adversely affecting the health-care system.
特殊条件下的高死亡率据美国有线电视新闻网（CNN）4日消息，近日，美国华盛顿州金县柯克兰（Kirkland）一家名为“生命护理中心”（Life Care Center）的长期护理机构中出现了新冠肺炎聚集性感染病例。
Life Care Center, a long-term care facility in Kirkland, Washington, reported a case of New Crown Pneumonia (CP) infection, CNN reported Thursday.
《纽约时报》称，美国的新冠肺炎死亡病例中有8例来自这里。
The New York Times says it is the source of eight deaths from pneumonia in the United States.
“生命护理中心”是美国一家连锁护理公司，在多个州都开设有护理中心，提供养老、康复、病人护理等服务。
Life Care is a chain of care companies in the United States that operates nursing centers in several states to provide care for the elderly, rehabilitation, and the sick.
美国医疗保险和医疗补助服务中心（CMS）5日宣布，将派出检查员，与美国疾控中心的专家一起调查该护理中心是否遵守了预防传染病的规定。
The Centers for Medical Insurance and Medical Assistance (CMS) announced Thursday that it would send inspectors to investigate with CDC experts whether the center complied with the rules for preventing infectious diseases.
柯克兰生命护理中心在2日发表声明称，当下该机构的所有入住人员以及与他们有关的人员，尤其是那些出现发烧、咳嗽与呼吸不畅等症状者“将继续接受密切观察”，目前该机构已暂停亲属探访。
"All residents and their associates, especially those suffering from fever, cough and shortness of breath," will continue to be closely monitored, "Kirkland said in a statement Tuesday.
CNN报道指出，该护理机构一名入住人员的儿子新冠病毒检测呈阳性，鉴于护理机构仍未对所有入住人员进行新冠病毒检测，部分入住人员的家属就此表示了担忧，希望对入住人员及其家属进行检测。
One of the residents' sons tested positive for the new crown virus and family members of some residents expressed concern that they would be tested for the virus and their family members, given that care facilities had not tested all residents for the virus, CNN reported.
柯克兰生命护理中心 Youtube视频截图此外，据《纽约时报》3日的报道，生命护理中心的首例新冠肺炎死亡病例2月24日从该机构转入西雅图哈伯维尤医院（Harborview Medical Center），并在2天后死亡，3月3日被确诊感染了新冠病毒。
The new Crown Pneumonia death at the Life Care Center was transferred from the facility to Harborview Medical Center in Seattle on Feb. 24 and died two days later after being diagnosed with the new crown virus, the New York Times reported Wednesday.
该医院发言人的苏珊·格雷格（Susan Gregg）表示，“鉴于50余名医护人员或在没有防护的情况下治疗病人，因而这些医护人员现在每天都要接受病毒检测。
Susan Gregg, a spokesman for the hospital, said: "With more than 50 paramedics or patients treated without protection, they are now tested for the virus on a daily basis.
”目前，108名哈伯维尤医院患者的亲眷朋友已被隔离。
So far, 108 relatives and friends of Huberville Hospital patients have been quarantined.
据悉，金县政府计划买下一幢汽车旅馆，用以隔离确诊患者。
It is reported that the county government plans to buy a motel to isolate confirmed patients.
《纽约时报》分析认为，新冠病毒可能已经在华盛顿州或其他地方传播了一段时间，但也许感染者的症状不严重，因此未被发现，使得病毒继续传播。
New York Times analysis suggests the virus may have been circulating in Washington state or elsewhere for some time, but the infection may not be so severe that it goes undetected, allowing the virus to spread.
但是，新冠肺炎对有基础疾病的老年人更加危险。
But new crown pneumonia is even more dangerous for older people with basic illnesses.
美国全国广播公司（NPR）称，华盛顿州的多数死亡病例年龄在70岁以上。
Most deaths in Washington state are over the age of 70, according to the NPR.
此外，华盛顿州伦顿（Renton）山谷医院（Valley Medical Center）一名员工也被确诊感染新冠病毒，该机构其他19名员工已接受了病毒检测，结果暂时呈阴性。
In addition, an employee at the Valley Medical Center in Washington state was also diagnosed with the new crown virus, and 19 of its other staff members were tested negative for the time being.
此前，韩国庆尚北道清道郡的大南医院也曾出现大面积感染事件，截至3月2日，与该院有关的病例达119例，死亡病例有7例，其中该院精神科102名住院病人中有99人确诊。
Earlier, South Korea Gyeongshan Northern Province Chungdaoshi county hospital in large-scale infection, as of March 2, 119 cases related to the hospital, seven cases of death, of which 102 inpatient psychiatric hospital confirmed.
2月初，新天地教会创始人李万熙哥哥的葬礼就在大南医院举办，而韩国目前的多数确诊病例均与新天地教会有关。
In early February, the funeral of Li Wanxi, founder of Xintiandi Church, was held at Da Nan Hospital, and most of the confirmed cases in South Korea are related to Xintiandi Church.
韩联社认为，精神科住院区封闭式管理的特殊性以及医院应对滞后，导致了该院病毒扩散速度和规模的失控。
According to KFW, the particularity of the closed management of psychiatric inpatient area and the lag of hospital response caused the spread of the virus out of control.
据美国《华盛顿邮报》报道，有韩国专家指出，该院精神科住院区条件较差，窗户封闭，通风不良，且患者的免疫力较低。
According to the Washington Post, a South Korean expert said the hospital's psychiatric inpatient section was in poor condition, with closed windows, poor ventilation and low immunity.
还有更多聚集性感染吗？西班牙、澳大利亚、英国等国也出现了护理机构和议员人员感染的情况，而且许多病例可能是“本土传播”而非输入性病例。
Are there more cases of sexually transmitted infections? Nursing institutions and members of parliament are also reported in countries such as Spain, Australia and the UK, and many cases are likely to be "home-grown" rather than imported.
外界担心这些地方是否也发生了聚集性感染事件。
There is concern about whether there are also cases of concentrated infections in these areas.
据路透社报道，西班牙首都马德里卫生部门3月5日表示，当地一所护理机构有10名入住人员和一名工作人员被确诊感染了新冠病毒，其中有一名99岁的老人已经去世。
A 99-year-old man has died after 10 residents and a staff member of a local care facility were diagnosed with the new crown virus, Reuters reported.
该机构的所有居住者都将接受新冠病毒检测，各种活动将被暂停。
All occupants of the facility will be tested for the new crown virus and activities will be suspended.
同时，马德里地区的护理机构将采取一系列预防性措施。
At the same time, care facilities in the Madrid region will take a series of preventive measures.
综合英国和澳大利亚媒体的报道，截止3月6日上午，澳大利亚悉尼的多萝西·亨德森小屋（Dorothy Henderson Lodge）老年护理中心已经有4名老人和2名工作人员确诊感染新冠病毒。
Dorothy Henderson Lodge's Geriatric Care Center in Sydney, Australia, had four elderly people and two staff members diagnosed with the new crown virus as of the morning of March 6, the British and Australian media reported.
3月4日，卫生部门确认还确诊该护理中心3日死亡的一名95岁老人感染了新冠病毒。
On 4 March, the health authorities confirmed that a 95-year-old man who had died at the care centre on 3 days had contracted the new crown virus.
英国也有医院出现了病人被感染的情况。
Hospitals in Britain have also seen cases of patients getting infected.
据英国广播公司（BBC）5日消息，英国伦敦的国王学院医院（King's College Hospital）有2名病人确诊感染新冠病毒。
Two patients at King's College Hospital in London were diagnosed with the new crown virus, BBC reported Friday.
一名家属表示，这2名确诊患者之前待在同一间病房内。
One family member said the two patients had previously been in the same ward.
目前，医院已封闭院内部分区域，限制员工与探访者进入确诊病例曾使用过的病房，并开始追踪这2名病例的密切接触者。
At present, the hospital has closed some areas of the compound, restricted access by staff and visitors to the wards where the confirmed cases had been used, and started to track down the close contacts of the two cases.
据英国《每日电讯报》4日消息，英格兰北部曼彻斯特一家医院也有1名患者确诊感染新冠病毒。
A man was diagnosed with the new crown virus at a hospital in Manchester in northern England, the Daily Telegraph reported Thursday.
英国卫生官员已就上述病例表示担忧，因为这些人未曾前往疫情高发国家，也未曾与其他确诊患者有过接触。
British health officials have expressed concern about the cases because they have not travelled to countries with a high incidence of the disease and have had no contact with other confirmed patients.
医护人员隔离或致人手短缺在病患被感染的同时，一些国家出现了医护人员感染的现象，这可能导致医护人员短缺，对应对疫情造成不利影响。
Medical Staff Isolated or Understaffed At the same time that patients are infected, there are cases of infection among health-care workers in some countries, which may lead to shortages of health-care personnel and adversely affect the response to the epidemic.
据西班牙《国家报》3日报道，西班牙北部巴斯克地区维多利亚市有2所医院5名医护人员感染新冠病毒，另有约100名医护人员正在隔离。
The Spanish newspaper El País reported Wednesday that five health-care workers in two hospitals in the northern Spanish city of Victoria were infected with the new crown virus, while about 100 others were being quarantined.
医院已要求住院的病人待在病房内，只允许一名亲属探望。
Hospitalized patients have been asked to stay in the wards and only one relative has been allowed to visit them.
此外，西班牙马德里和安达卢西亚两个地区的政府也要求共200多名曾经接触过确诊病例的医护人员待在家中，以防病毒在医院中传染。
In addition, the Governments of Madrid and Andalusia, Spain, required more than 200 health-care workers who had been in contact with confirmed cases to stay at home to prevent the spread of the virus in hospitals.
西班牙卫生部长3日已经建议取消近期的医学会议，以保证医护人员人手。
Spain's Health Minister on the 3-day proposal to cancel the recent medical conference to ensure that health-care workers.
另据《卫报》和《悉尼先驱晨报》的消息，澳大利亚新南威尔士州4日也确诊了至少有 2名医生感染新冠病毒，其中一人接触过新冠病毒感染者后被确诊。
New South Wales confirmed at least two doctors with the new crown virus, including one who was diagnosed with the virus, the Guardian and Sydney Morning Herald reported.
据报道，这2名医生所在的2所医院的80多名员工需要在家隔离14天。
It was reported that more than 80 employees in the two hospitals where the two doctors were working had to be kept in isolation for 14 days.
新南威尔士州卫生官员克丽·钱特（Kerry Chant）表示，已经有医院的医护人员来支援受影响的医院，但许多人需要加班。
New South Wales health official Kerry Chant said hospital staff had come to support the affected hospitals, but many had to work overtime.
她还说，由于目前要应对流感，现在医院的工作会很繁忙。
She added that hospitals will now be busy with the flu.
本期编辑 邢潭推荐阅读。
